563. quid censes? sc. eum locutum esse. Philto is true to his promise not to reveal what Stasimus has said. Accordingly he turns aside Lesbonicus’ question. ‘What do you suppose (he said)?' He talked on what was naturally uppermost in his mind, viz, how he could get his freedom.
